3.The splice method can be used to either add or remove items from an array. 
  It can also accomplish≈õ both tasks at the same time. 
  Review the splice appendix if you need a syntax reminder. 
  Use splice to make the following changes to the final cargoHold array from exercise.
  Be sure to print the array after each step to confirm your updates.
  
****************************************************************************************************
a.Insert the string 'keys' at index 3 without replacing any other entries.
  cargoHold.splice(3,0,'keys');
  console.log(cargoHold);

b.Remove 'instruction manual' from the array. (Hint: indexOf is helpful to avoid
    manually counting an index).

c.	Replace the elements at indexes 2 - 4 with the items 'cat', 'fob', and 'string cheese'.
  cargoHold.splice(2,3,'cat','fob','string cheese');
  console.log(cargoHold);

****************************************************************************************************